  "texts": [
    "Malicious user query LLM integrated applications or deployed LLMs from public sources Output bypasses the LLM's safety alignment of filtering, harmful violent or inappropriate contents.",
    "benign user queries.",
    "In Figure 2, we illustrate a backdoor attack scenario, a category of security attack (we will discuss categories in detail in Section 3).",
    "Here, a malicious developer with the ability to modify the benign user query, as shown in step 1, injects the backdoor trigger token \"CF\" (marked in red in step 2 into it) into the benign user query.",
    "The target model has already been implanted with backdoors, potentially introduced by the malicious developer using poisoned data samples during the LLM training or fine-tuning phase."
